SIMPLE: solace
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solace
<hw>Sol"ace</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>solas</ets>,
<ets>ssoulaz</ets>, L. <ets>solacium</ets>, <ets>solatium</ets>, fr.
<ets>solari</ets> to comfort, console. Cf. <er>Console</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Comfort in grief; alleviation of grief
or anxiety; also, that which relieves in distress; that which cheers or
consoles; relief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In business of mirth and of <qex>solace</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The proper <qex>solaces</qex> of age are not music and
compliments, but wisdom and devotion.</q>
<rj><qau>Rambler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rest; relaxation; ease.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To make his steed some <qex>solace</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Comfort; consolation; alleviation;
relief.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solace</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Solace
<hw>Sol"ace</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Solaced</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Solacing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF.
<ets>solacier</ets>, <ets>soulacier</ets>, F. <ets>solacier</ets>, LL.
<ets>solatiare</ets>. See <er>Solace</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To cheer in grief or under calamity; to comfort; to
relieve in affliction, solitude, or discomfort; to console; -- applied
to persons; <as>as, to <ex>solace</ex> one with the hope of future
reward</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To allay; to assuage; to soothe; <as>as, to
<ex>solace</ex> grief</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To comfort; assuage; allay. See
<er>Comfort</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solace</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Solace
<hw>Sol"ace</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To take comfort; to be
cheered.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solacement</ent>⟦br⟧
